 |-----------|-------|----------|\n71: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## File Structure\n76: \n77: ```\n78: [TO BE FILLED: Expected file structure]\n79: ```\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## Dependencies\n84: \n85: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n86: |---------|---------|---------|\n87: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## Implementation Notes\n92: \n93: [TO BE FILLED: Key implementation details and patterns]\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## References\n98: \n99: - [TO BE FILLED: Related documents and external resources]\n\n(End of file - total 99 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Brief overview of the component and its role in the system]\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/design.md","time":{"start":1775863373279,"end":1775863373311}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863373314,"sessionID":"ses_2864bbb32ffe3jJEubZGUoaXIp","part":{"id":"prt_d79b498e1001cvhizCkrKUZaY6","messageID":"msg_d79b47a17001W6TvKYhYbxuL8m","sessionID":"ses_2864bbb32ffe3jJEubZGUoaXIp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-dcfbe0164b7a4e34a8dfdb35945a0c84","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-0 |\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: [TO BE FILLED: Define scope of implementation]\n16: \n17: ## Out of Scope\n18: \n19: [TO BE FILLED: Items explicitly out of scope]\n20: \n21: ## Dependencies\n22: \n23: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n24: |------------|---------|---------|\n25: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n26: \n27: ## Deliverables\n28: \n29: | File | Description |\n30: |------|-------------|\n31: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n32: \n33: ## Acceptance Criteria\n34: \n35: - [ ] [TO BE FILLED: Acceptance criteria]\n36: \n37: ## References\n38: \n39: - [TO BE FILLED: Related ARs and documents]\n\n(End of file - total 39 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-0 |\n\n## Scope\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Define scope of implementation]\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Items explicitly out of scope]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/spec.md","time":{"start":1775863373281,"end":1775863373313}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863373336,"sessionID":"ses_2864bbb32ffe3jJEubZGUoaXIp","part":{"id":"prt_d79b49dc1001e8rwAAD3dGEtGe","messageID":"msg_d79b47a17001W6TvKYhYbxuL8m","sessionID":"ses_2864bbb32ffe3jJEubZGUoaXIp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b6640a607a9a44599c9da0a3a5dc75ea","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Extend PicoD's file management capabilities with comprehensive file system manipulation APIs including file deletion, directory creation, file copy/move, permissions modification, and archive operations (tar/zip) for AI agent workspace management. This builds upon AR-015's basic file operations (upload, list, download) with additional REST endpoints for full-featured workspace file management.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Delete request/response structures\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define structures for file/directory deletion request and response.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: DeleteRequest struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `DeleteRequest` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` (wildcard path from URL)\n26:   - `Recursive bool` with JSON tag `recursive` (for directory deletion)\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: DeleteResponse struct definition\n29: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n30: - **WHEN** reading the `DeleteResponse` struct\n31: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n32:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path`\n33:   - `Deleted bool` with JSON tag `deleted`\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: Delete handler\n38: \n39: The system SHALL implement file/directory deletion handler with recursive support.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler path extraction\n42: - **GIVEN** DELETE request to `/api/files/*path`\n43: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n44: - **THEN** `c.Param(\"path\")` SHALL extract wildcard path\n45: - AND leading `/` SHALL be stripped from path\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler path sanitization\n48: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n49: - **WHEN** processing delete path\n50: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, strippedPath)` SHALL be called\n51: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler file existence check\n54: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n55: - **WHEN** checking path\n56: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n57: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if path not found\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler file deletion\n60: - **GIVEN** path is a regular file\n61: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n62: - **THEN** `os.Remove(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n63: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `DeleteResponse`\n64: - AND `Deleted` SHALL be `true`\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler directory deletion with recursive flag\n67: - **GIVEN** path is a directory AND `Recursive` is `true`\n68: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n69: - **THEN** `os.RemoveAll(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n70: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `DeleteResponse`\n71: - AND `Deleted` SHALL be `true`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler directory deletion without recursive flag\n74: - **GIVEN** path is a directory AND `Recursive` is `false`\n75: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n76: - **THEN** `os.Remove(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n77: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if directory is non-empty\n78: - AND error message SHALL indicate directory is not empty\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler empty directory deletion\n81: - **GIVEN** path is an empty directory AND `Recursive` is `false`\n82: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n83: - **THEN** `os.Remove(sanitizedPath)` SHALL succeed\n84: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Create directory request/response structures\n89: \n90: The system SHALL define structures for directory creation request and response.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryRequest struct definition\n93: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n94: - **WHEN** reading the `CreateDirectoryRequest` struct\n95: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n96:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n97:   - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode` (optional octal string)\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryResponse struct definition\n100: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n101: - **WHEN** reading the `CreateDirectoryResponse` struct\n102: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n103:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path`\n104:   - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode`\n105:   - `Created bool` with JSON tag `created`\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Create directory handler\n110: \n111: The system SHALL implement directory creation handler with nested support.\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler request binding\n114: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/directory`\n115: - **WHEN** CreateDirectoryHandler processes request\n116: - **THEN** `CreateDirectoryRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n117: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler path sanitization\n120: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n121: - **WHEN** processing directory path\n122: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Path)` SHALL be called\n123: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler mode parsing\n126: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n127: - **WHEN** parsing directory mode\n128: - **THEN** `parseFileMode(req.Mode)` SHALL be called\n129: - AND default mode SHALL be `defaultDirMode` (`0755`) if mode empty/invalid\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler nested directory creation\n132: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n133: - **WHEN** creating directory\n134: - **THEN** `os.MkdirAll(sanitizedPath, os.FileMode(mode))` SHALL be called\n135: - AND parent directories SHALL be created if not existing\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler already exists\n138: - **GIVEN** directory already exists\n139: - **WHEN** CreateDirectoryHandler processes request\n140: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n141: - AND `Created` SHALL be `false`\n142: - AND existing directory mode SHALL be preserved\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler response\n145: - **GIVEN** successful directory creation\n146: - **WHEN** CreateDirectoryHandler completes\n147: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n148: - AND `CreateDirectoryResponse` SHALL include path and mode\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ### Requirement: Copy request/response structures\n153: \n154: The system SHALL define structures for file/directory copy request and response.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: CopyRequest struct definition\n157: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n158: - **WHEN** reading the `CopyRequest` struct\n159: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n160:   - `Source string` with JSON tag `source` and `binding:\"required\"`\n161:   - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest` and `binding:\"required\"`\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: CopyResponse struct definition\n164: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n165: - **WHEN** reading the `CopyResponse` struct\n166: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n167:   - `Source string` with JSON tag `source`\n168:   - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest`\n169:   - `Copied bool` with JSON tag `copied`\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ### Requirement: Copy handler\n174: \n175: The system SHALL implement file/directory copy handler with recursive support.\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler request binding\n178: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/copy`\n179: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n180: - **THEN** `CopyRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n181: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler source sanitization\n184: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n185: - **WHEN** processing source path\n186: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Source)` SHALL be called\n187: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler destination sanitization\n190: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n191: - **WHEN** processing destination path\n192: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Dest)` SHALL be called\n193: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler source existence check\n196: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n197: - **WHEN** checking source path\n198: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n199: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler file copy\n202: - **GIVEN** source is a regular file\n203: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n204: - **THEN** `os.Open(source)` SHALL open source file\n205: - AND `os.Create(dest)` SHALL create destination file\n206: - AND `io.Copy(destFile, srcFile)` SHALL copy content\n207: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `CopyResponse`\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler directory copy\n210: - **GIVEN** source is a directory\n211: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n212: - **THEN** `filepath.Walk(source, walkFunc)` SHALL be called\n213: - AND walkFunc SHALL copy each file to destination with relative path\n214: - AND directory structure SHALL be preserved\n215: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler symlink handling\n218: - **GIVEN** source contains symlinks\n219: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n220: - **THEN** symlinks SHALL be skipped OR target SHALL be resolved\n221: - AND symlink escape SHALL be validated via `sanitizePath`\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler destination exists\n224: - **GIVEN** destination path already exists\n225: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n226: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n227: - AND error message SHALL indicate destination exists\n228: \n229: ---\n230: \n231: ### Requirement: Move request/response structures\n232: \n233: The system SHALL define structures for file/directory move request and response.\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: MoveRequest struct definition\n236: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n237: - **WHEN** reading the `MoveRequest` struct\n238: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n239:   - `Source string` with JSON tag `source` and `binding:\"required\"`\n240:   - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest` and `binding:\"required\"`\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: MoveResponse struct definition\n243: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n244: - **WHEN** reading the `MoveResponse` struct\n245: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n246:   - `Source string` with JSON tag `source`\n247:   - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest`\n248:   - `Moved bool` with JSON tag `moved`\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ### Requirement: Move handler\n253: \n254: The system SHALL implement file/directory move/rename handler.\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler request binding\n257: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/move`\n258: - **WHEN** MoveFileHandler processes request\n259: - **THEN** `MoveRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n260: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler source sanitization\n263: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n264: - **WHEN** processing source path\n265: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Source)` SHALL be called\n266: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler destination sanitization\n269: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n270: - **WHEN** processing destination path\n271: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Dest)` SHALL be called\n272: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n273: \n274: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler source existence check\n275: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n276: - **WHEN** checking source path\n277: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n278: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler rename operation\n281: - **GIVEN** valid source and destination paths\n282: - **WHEN** MoveFileHandler processes request\n283: - **THEN** `os.Rename(sanitizedSource, sanitizedDest)` SHALL be called\n284: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `MoveResponse`\n285: \n286: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler cross-filesystem move\n287: - **GIVEN** source and destination on different filesystems\n288: - **WHEN** `os.Rename` returns cross-device error\n289: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n290: - AND error message SHALL indicate cross-filesystem move not supported\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler destination exists\n293: - **GIVEN** destination path already exists\n294: - **WHEN** MoveFileHandler processes request\n295: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n296: - AND error message SHALL indicate destination exists\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: ### Requirement: Modify permissions request/response structures\n301: \n302: The system SHALL define structures for permissions modification request and response.\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsRequest struct definition\n305: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n306: - **WHEN** reading the `ModifyPermissionsRequest` struct\n307: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n308:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` (wildcard path from URL)\n309:   - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode` and `binding:\"required\"` (octal string)\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsResponse struct definition\n312: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n313: - **WHEN** reading the `ModifyPermissionsResponse` struct\n314: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n315:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path`\n316:   - `OldMode string` with JSON tag `old_mode`\n317:   - `NewMode string` with JSON tag `new_mode`\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n321: ### Requirement: Modify permissions handler\n322: \n323: The system SHALL implement file/directory permissions modification handler.\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler path extraction\n326: - **GIVEN** PATCH request to `/api/files/*path`\n327: - **WHEN** ModifyPermissionsHandler processes request\n328: - **THEN** `c.Param(\"path\")` SHALL extract wildcard path\n329: - AND leading `/` SHALL be stripped from path\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler request binding\n332: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n333: - **WHEN** ModifyPermissionsHandler processes request\n334: - **THEN** `ModifyPermissionsRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n335: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n336: \n337: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler path sanitization\n338: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n339: - **WHEN** processing modify path\n340: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, strippedPath)` SHALL be called\n341: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler file existence check\n344: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n345: - **WHEN** checking path\n346: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n347: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if path not found\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler old mode retrieval\n350: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n351: - **WHEN** getting old permissions\n352: - **THEN** `info.Mode().Perm()` SHALL extract current mode\n353: - AND old mode SHALL be formatted as octal string\n354: \n355: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler mode parsing\n356: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n357: - **WHEN** parsing new mode\n358: - **THEN** `parseFileMode(req.Mode)` SHALL be called\n359: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if mode invalid\n360: - AND mode SHALL be validated against `maxFileMode` (`0777`)\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler chmod operation\n363: - **GIVEN** valid new mode\n364: - **WHEN** ModifyPermissionsHandler processes request\n365: - **THEN** `os.Chmod(sanitizedPath, os.FileMode(newMode))` SHALL be called\n366: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `ModifyPermissionsResponse`\n367: - AND response SHALL include old and new modes\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ### Requirement: Archive request/response structures\n372: \n373: The system SHALL define structures for archive creation request and response.\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: ArchiveRequest struct definition\n376: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n377: - **WHEN** reading the `ArchiveRequest` struct\n378: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n379:   - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n380:   - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n381:   - `Format string` with JSON tag `format` (optional: \"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\")\n382: \n383: #### Scenario: ArchiveResponse struct definition\n384: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n385: - **WHEN** reading the `ArchiveResponse` struct\n386: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n387:   - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path`\n388:   - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path`\n389:   - `Format string` with JSON tag `format`\n390:   - `Size int64` with JSON tag `size`\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ### Requirement: Archive handler\n395: \n396: The system SHALL implement archive creation handler with tar/zip support.\n397: \n398: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler request binding\n399: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/archive`\n400: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler processes request\n401: - **THEN** `ArchiveRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n402: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler source path sanitization\n405: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n406: - **WHEN** processing source path\n407: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.SourcePath)` SHALL be called\n408: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n409: \n410: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler destination path sanitization\n411: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n412: - **WHEN** processing destination path\n413: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.DestPath)` SHALL be called\n414: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n415: \n416: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler source existence check\n417: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n418: - **WHEN** checking source path\n419: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n420: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n421: \n422: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler format detection\n423: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n424: - **WHEN** determining archive format\n425: - **THEN** format SHALL be detected from `req.Format` OR `filepath.Ext(req.DestPath)`\n426: - AND supported formats SHALL be `allowedArchiveFormats` (\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\")\n427: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned for unsupported format\n428: \n429: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler tar creation\n430: - **GIVEN** format is \"tar\" or \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\"\n431: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler creates archive\n432: - **THEN** `tar.Create` SHALL be used with `archive/tar` package\n433: - AND `filepath.Walk(source, walkFunc)` SHALL walk source\n434: - AND each entry SHALL be added with relative path\n435: - AND gzip SHALL be applied for \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\" format via `compress/gzip`\n436: \n437: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler zip creation\n438: - **GIVEN** format is \"zip\"\n439: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler creates archive\n440: - **THEN** `zip.Create` SHALL be used with `archive/zip` package\n441: - AND `filepath.Walk(source, walkFunc)` SHALL walk source\n442: - AND each entry SHALL be added with relative path\n443: \n444: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler response\n445: - **GIVEN** successful archive creation\n446: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler completes\n447: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n448: - AND `ArchiveResponse` SHALL include source path, destination path, format, and size\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ### Requirement: Extract request/response structures\n453: \n454: The system SHALL define structures for archive extraction request and response.\n455: \n456: #### Scenario: ExtractRequest struct definition\n457: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n458: - **WHEN** reading the `ExtractRequest` struct\n459: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n460:   - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n461:   - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path` (optional: defaults to parent directory)\n462: \n463: #### Scenario: ExtractResponse struct definition\n464: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n465: - **WHEN** reading the `ExtractResponse` struct\n466: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n467:   - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path`\n468:   - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path`\n469:   - `Files []FileEntry` with JSON tag `files` (extracted files list)\n470: \n471: ---\n472: \n473: ### Requirement: Extract handler\n474: \n475: The system SHALL implement archive extraction handler with path escape protection.\n476: \n477: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler request binding\n478: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/extract`\n479: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler processes request\n480: - **THEN** `ExtractRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n481: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n482: \n483: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler source path sanitization\n484: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n485: - **WHEN** processing source path\n486: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.SourcePath)` SHALL be called\n487: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n488: \n489: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler destination path resolution\n490: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n491: - **WHEN** `req.DestPath` is empty\n492: - **THEN** `filepath.Dir(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be used as destination\n493: - WHEN `req.DestPath` is non-empty\n494: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.DestPath)` SHALL be called\n495: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n496: \n497: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler source existence check\n498: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n499: - **WHEN** checking source path\n500: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n501: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n502: \n503: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler size limit check\n504: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n505: - **WHEN** checking archive size\n506: - **THEN** `os.Stat(source).Size()` SHALL get archive size\n507: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if size > `maxArchiveSize` (`100 << 20`)\n508: - AND error message SHALL indicate archive exceeds size limit\n509: \n510: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler format detection\n511: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n512: - **WHEN** determining archive format\n513: - **THEN** format SHALL be detected from `filepath.Ext(req.SourcePath)`\n514: - AND supported formats SHALL be `allowedArchiveFormats`\n515: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned for unsupported format\n516: \n517: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler tar extraction\n518: - **GIVEN** format is \"tar\" or \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\"\n519: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts archive\n520: - **THEN** `tar.NewReader` SHALL be used with `archive/tar` package\n521: - AND gzip SHALL be decompressed for \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\" via `compress/gzip`\n522: - AND each entry SHALL be extracted to destination\n523: \n524: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler zip extraction\n525: - **GIVEN** format is \"zip\"\n526: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts archive\n527: - **THEN** `zip.OpenReader` SHALL be used with `archive/zip` package\n528: - AND each entry SHALL be extracted to destination\n529: \n530: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler entry path sanitization\n531: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n532: - **WHEN** extracting each archive entry\n533: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(destination, entry.Name)` SHALL be called for each entry path\n534: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if entry path escapes workspace\n535: - AND entry path SHALL reject `..` components\n536: \n537: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler directory entry creation\n538: - **GIVEN** archive entry is a directory\n539: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts entry\n540: - **THEN** `os.MkdirAll(entryPath, entry.Mode)` SHALL create directory\n541: - AND nested directories SHALL be created\n542: \n543: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler file entry creation\n544: - **GIVEN** archive entry is a file\n545: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts entry\n546: - **THEN** `os.Create(entryPath)` SHALL create file\n547: - AND entry content SHALL be written via `io.Copy`\n548: - AND file mode SHALL be set via `os.Chmod`\n549: \n550: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler response\n551: - **GIVEN** successful extraction\n552: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler completes\n553: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n554: - AND `ExtractResponse` SHALL include source path, destination path, and extracted files list\n555: \n556: ---\n557: \n558: ### Requirement: Route registration extension\n559: \n560: The system SHALL extend route registration with new file management endpoints.\n561: \n562: #### Scenario: New file management routes registration\n563: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n564: - **WHEN** registering routes\n565: - **THEN** `/api/files/*path` SHALL be registered with `DeleteFileHandler` (DELETE)\n566: - AND `/api/files/directory` SHALL be registered with `CreateDirectoryHandler` (POST)\n567: - AND `/api/files/copy` SHALL be registered with `CopyFileHandler` (POST)\n568: - AND `/api/files/move` SHALL be registered with `MoveFileHandler` (POST)\n569: - AND `/api/files/*path` SHALL be registered with `ModifyPermissionsHandler` (PATCH)\n570: - AND `/api/files/archive` SHALL be registered with `ArchiveHandler` (POST)\n571: - AND `/api/files/extract` SHALL be registered with `ExtractHandler` (POST)\n572: - AND all routes SHALL use existing JWT auth middleware\n573: \n574: ---\n575: \n576: ### Requirement: Constants\n577: \n578: The system SHALL define constants for file management behavior configuration.\n579: \n580: #### Scenario: defaultDirMode constant\n581: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n582: - **WHEN** reading constants\n583: - **THEN** `defaultDirMode` SHALL be `0755`\n584: \n585: #### Scenario: maxArchiveSize constant\n586: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n587: - **WHEN** reading constants\n588: - **THEN** `maxArchiveSize` SHALL be `100 << 20` (100 MiB)\n589: \n590: #### Scenario: allowedArchiveFormats constant\n591: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n592: - **WHEN** reading constants\n593: - **THEN** `allowedArchiveFormats` SHALL be `[\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\"]`\n594: \n595: ---\n596: \n597: ### Requirement: Error handling\n598: \n599: The system SHALL handle errors with appropriate HTTP status codes and messages.\n600: \n601: #### Scenario: Delete non-empty directory without recursive error\n602: - **GIVEN** directory is non-empty AND `Recursive` is `false`\n603: - **WHEN** delete fails\n604: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n605: - AND body SHALL indicate directory is not empty\n606: \n607: #### Scenario: Cross-filesystem move error\n608: - **GIVEN** `os.Rename` returns cross-device error\n609: - **WHEN** MoveFileHandler encounters error\n610: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n611: - AND body SHALL indicate cross-filesystem move not supported\n612: \n613: #### Scenario: Archive size exceeded error\n614: - **GIVEN** archive size > `maxArchiveSize`\n615: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler detects size violation\n616: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n617: - AND body SHALL indicate archive exceeds size limit\n618: \n619: #### Scenario: Unsupported archive format error\n620: - **GIVEN** unsupported archive format\n621: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler or ExtractHandler detects format\n622: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n623: - AND body SHALL indicate unsupported format\n624: \n625: #### Scenario: Archive entry path escape error\n626: - **GIVEN** archive entry path escapes workspace\n627: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler detects path escape\n628: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n629: - AND body SHALL indicate invalid entry path\n630: \n631: ---\n632: \n633: ## Constants Summary\n634: \n635: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n636: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n637: | `defaultDirMode` | `0755` | `files.go` | Default directory creation mode |\n638: | `maxArchiveSize` | `100 << 20` | `archive.go` | Maximum archive size for extraction (100 MiB) |\n639: | `allowedArchiveFormats` | `[\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\"]` | `archive.go` | Supported archive formats |\n640: \n641: ---\n642: \n643: ## API Endpoints Summary\n644: \n645: | Endpoint | Method | Auth | Handler |\n646: |----------|--------|------|---------|\n647: | `/api/files/*path` | DELETE | JWT | `DeleteFileHandler` |\n648: | `/api/files/directory` | POST | JWT | `CreateDirectoryHandler` |\n649: | `/api/files/copy` | POST | JWT | `CopyFileHandler` |\n650: | `/api/files/move` | POST | JWT | `MoveFileHandler` |\n651: | `/api/files/*path` | PATCH | JWT | `ModifyPermissionsHandler` |\n652: | `/api/files/archive` | POST | JWT | `ArchiveHandler` |\n653: | `/api/files/extract` | POST | JWT | `ExtractHandler` |\n654: \n655: ---\n656: \n657: ## File Changes Summary\n658: \n659: | File | Action | Description |\n660: |------|--------|-------------|\n661: | `pkg/picod/files.go` | Extend | Add `DeleteRequest`, `DeleteResponse`, `CreateDirectoryRequest`, `CreateDirectoryResponse`, `CopyRequest`, `CopyResponse`, `MoveRequest`, `MoveResponse`, `ModifyPermissionsRequest`, `ModifyPermissionsResponse`, and handlers |\n662: | `pkg/picod/archive.go` | Create | `ArchiveRequest`, `ArchiveResponse`, `ExtractRequest`, `ExtractResponse`, `ArchiveHandler`, `ExtractHandler` |\n663: | `pkg/picod/server.go` | Extend | Register new file management routes |\n664: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Extend | Unit tests for new handlers |\n665: \n666: ---\n667: \n668: ## References\n669: \n670: - `changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md` — Original PicoD implementation\n671: - `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` — Path security logic\n672: - [Go archive/tar](https://pkg.go.dev/archive/tar)\n673: - [Go archive/zip](https://pkg.go.dev/archive/zip)\n674: - [Go compress/gzip](https://pkg.go.dev/compress/gzip)\n\n(End of file - total 674 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nExtend PicoD's file management capabilities with comprehensive file system manipulation APIs including file deletion, directory creation, file copy/move, permissions modification, and archive operations (tar/zip) for AI agent workspace management. This builds upon AR-015's basic file operations (upload, list, download) with additional REST endpoints for full-featured workspace file management.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Delete request/response structures\n\nThe system SHALL define structures for file/directory deletion request and response.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775863373283,"end":1775863373315}}}}
